snippet: Ledecky, an 18-year-old American, won the 1,500-meter freestyle at the swimming world championships and then competed in a 200-meter freestyle semifinal, all in less than 50 minutes.
abstract: American swimmer Katie Ledecky, competing at swimming world championships, sets world record in 1,500-meter freestyle final only 29 minutes before placing sixth and qualifying for final in 200-meter freestyle; succeeds at feat no woman has ever attempted at sport's highest level.
lead_paragraph: Ledecky, an 18-year-old American, won the 1,500-meter freestyle at the swimming world championships and then competed in a 200-meter freestyle semifinal, all in less than 50 minutes.

headline.main: Katie Ledecky Sets Another Record, Then Returns to Pool
headline.print_headline: Another Record, Then Right Back Into the Pool
